    <text>
        <front/>
        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="#f0001"/>
            <dateline>
                <hi rendition="#et">LONDON, Oct 17.</hi>
            </dateline>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">extent and population of america.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The following estimate of the extent,<lb break="yes"/>in square leagues, and population, of the<lb break="yes"/>Continent of America in 1822, was late-<lb break="no"/>ly transmitted by Baron de Humboldt<lb break="yes"/>from Paris, to President Bolivar, with<lb break="yes"/>the accompanying letter:</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell> Sqr. Leagues</cell>
                        <cell> Population</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mexico, or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75,830</cell>
                        <cell>6,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Guatemala</cell>
                        <cell>16,740</cell>
                        <cell>1,600,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Cuba and Puerto Rico</cell>
                        <cell>4,430</cell>
                        <cell>800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="3">Colombia <list rendition="#leftBraced">
                            <item>Venezuela</item>
                            <item>New Granada</item>
                        </list></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>33,700</cell>
                        <cell>900,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>58,250</cell>
                        <cell>1,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell/></row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Peru</cell>
                        <cell>42,150</cell>
                        <cell>1,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Chili</cell>
                        <cell>14,240</cell>
                        <cell>1,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell>126,770</cell>
                        <cell>2,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total formerly Spanish</cell>
                        <cell>372,110</cell>
                        <cell>16,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   United States</cell>
                        <cell>125,440</cell>
                        <cell>10,200,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256,990</cell>
                        <cell>4,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                
                <p>The above surfaces have been calculat-<lb break="no"/>ed with great care, on maps
                    rectified by<lb break="yes"/>astronomical observations. The calcula-<lb
                        break="no"/>tions have been several times repeated by<lb break="yes"/>M.
                    Mathieu, member of the Board of<lb break="yes"/>Longitude, as well as by myself.
                        The<lb break="yes"/>results differ from those published in<lb break="yes"
                    />1809, in the Political Essay on Mexico.<lb break="yes"/>Then the inhabited
                    parts alone had been<lb break="yes"/>calculated, without including the desert<lb
                        break="yes"/>regions, over which the independent<lb break="yes"/>tribes of
                    the indegenous inhabitants wan-<lb break="no"/>der. Now the whole extent of
                        each<lb break="yes"/>country, to its furthest limits, has been<lb
                        break="yes"/>measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts<lb break="yes"/>of <hi rendition="#i"
                        >ci-devant</hi> Spanish America is very un-<lb break="no"/>certain,
                    nevertheless each portion has<lb break="yes"/>been calculated according to the
                        latest<lb break="yes"/>data which have reached me. The pre-<lb break="no"
                    />sent estimate ought to be considered in<lb break="yes"/>the same light as all
                    my other works on<lb break="yes"/>America; they are no other than essays,<lb
                        break="yes"/>in which every thing will have to be done<lb break="yes"
                    /><cb/>over again. Statistical calculations can<lb break="yes"/>only be rendered
                    perfect by degrees, in<lb break="yes"/>like manner as the elements of
                        meteoro-<lb break="no"/>logical and astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;Spain contains 16,094<lb break="yes"
                    />square leagues&#x2014;Europe contains 304,710<lb break="yes"/>square leagues,
                    and the whole of South-<lb break="no"/>ern America 581,891 square leagues.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">(Signed) HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
